node.text:
As 2020 comes to a close (thank the lord) I’m extra grateful to be standing in the space I’ve always dreamed of. I couldn’t have done it without my team who loves this business as if it were their own. So many sleepless nights, tears and hard work which all are worth it. Yesterday at the shop I had my niece and daughter working the register, my sister in law and friend restocking our shelves and I got to meet so many of you that are thanking me for inspiring them. I may have shed some (more) tears and thought to myself this is it. The dream. I hope I see you real soon at the shop or online ❤️

Thank you @chr15hurd for making me look slightly less awkward on camera.

node.title: Our new Studio and At Home Shop!

node.text: Truth is I was supposed to leave for Vegas today with my entire team to head to market. Something in my gut told me it wasn’t the right time to go so we are making the best of it and hoping for a big @shopeyeforpretty day so we can help @womenforafghanwomen. If you can’t make it, there are still other ways to support which I’ll put in stories today!

node.text:
Tomorrow @shopeyeforpretty is open from 1-4! We have new art (shown here), a few vintage tiny rugs and lots of new decor items. Twenty percent of our proceeds will be donated to @womenforafghanwomen and that includes any online purchases this weekend. Thanks for your support!

📷 @amybartlam

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Eye For Pretty on August 17, 2021 tagging @amybartlam. May be an image of 1 person and kitchen.

node.text:
Nothing is better than a photo shoot day but close second is an install day! Our Orinda project is wrapping up and today some furniture items are finally getting delivered. Follow along in stories to see what’s new!

P.S. Missing my long hair again. 

📷 @amybartlam

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Eye For Pretty on August 12, 2021 tagging @amybartlam. May be an image of kitchen.

node.text:
Raise your hand if you’re looking forward to clean kitchens again and kids not asking for food every two minutes? Yesterday I got in 75% of my to-do’s before the kids got home and was feeling pretty good until I realized my daughter had early dismissal and I didn’t grab her. Thank god for friends! Let’s see how I do today 🤞🏻

📷 @amybartlam

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Eye For Pretty on August 09, 2021 tagging @amybartlam, @studiomcgee, @mcgeeandco, and @shopeyeforpretty. May be an image of furniture and bedroom.

node.text:
Does anyone else say “when the kids go back to school I’ll do this.” Well, the kids are going back to school tomorrow (praise) and now I have NO excuse not to get to the hundreds of items on my to-do list. They range from anything like workout every morning to finish that podcast interview to update our portfolio. Tomorrow my to do item will be, hold it together when I send my middle schooler on the bus. Small tasks. They add up to the bigger ones. Luckily never on my list… make the bed. @eye4petty has that one DOWN.

And because you will ask, I will have an ETA on skinny benches soon! 

📷 @amybartlam

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Eye For Pretty on August 07, 2021 tagging @apriljrecinos. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
Wishing it was a sunny Saturday morning but the smoke and haze is so bad again in CA. I heard July was one of the worst months in history for fires here and I know we have a long season ahead of us. Praying for all those directly affected and our firefighters on the front lines. Also praying for some freak storms to give some relief 🙏🏻 

📷 @amybartlam

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Eye For Pretty on August 06, 2021 tagging @jessicabrydsonphotography. May be an image of furniture and kitchen.

node.text:
Another view of this gorgeous kitchen/dining space! These chairs are some of our best sellers and the curved back is actually very comfortable. Tap to shop some of the items seen here and I’ll link the table in stories!

📷 @jessicabrydsonphotography

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Eye For Pretty on August 05, 2021 tagging @amybartlam, and @bedrosianstile. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
In case you missed it, we are HIRING! We’ve been really blessed to see our industry thrive during these uncertain times and I appreciate every call and inquiry that comes in. However, we can only take on a limited amount of new projects unless I grow my team (which is no easy feat.) I would love to bring on all you design lovers but I am looking for someone with a couple years experience and AutoCAD capabilities. If you are a solo designer and getting overwhelmed, think about joining an amazing team! 

📷 @amybartlam

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Eye For Pretty on August 02, 2021 tagging @palecekdesign. May be an image of furniture and kitchen.

node.text:
The countdown is officially on! One more week until school starts here and I’m trying to wrap my brain around school supplies, bus schedules and packing lunches every day 😆 Summer always goes way too fast but I am someone who thrives on routines so I’m looking forward to getting into a rhythm again. I’m also REALLY looking forward to new kitchens getting completed! They will all be totally different and have unique elements I know you’ll love. In the meantime, the #delamigoremodel will always be a favorite.

📷 @amybartlam

node.text:
Headed out to celebrate one of my favorites 40th birthday @lindsaytatedesigns! She’s also a talented designer but even more importantly, my best friend for life. Get ready for #designersgonewild in stories. I’m kidding but last time I posted a reel of her dancing it basically went viral 😆 

📷 @nicolediannephoto

The prettiest view this morning. It might be the sparkle on the floor for me ✨ As much as I love moody, my first love will always be light and bright.

📷 @amybartlam
